The package does not include hosted compute, bundled model credits, API keys,
provider accounts, private Hasna infrastructure, or telemetry endpoints.
Remote model use is bring-your-own-key and is disabled unless the operator
explicitly configures a provider and cost cap.

The npm package name for the public release is @hasna/matematica.
The CLI command is matematica.
The public source repository is https://github.com/hasna/matematica.

Third-party dependencies are resolved by the operator's package manager from
their own licenses. See package.json and the lockfile for dependency names and
versions.
